transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, I had a question for you regarding the prescription that I just received in the last—

Speaker 2: day or so.

Speaker 1: I can take a look into your account.

Speaker 2: What's your last name and a zip code?

Speaker 1: Last name is Lester, L-E-S-T-E-R, and did you say zip code?

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: 98012.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I pulled up your profile here.

Speaker 1: I do see your latest prescription was for the Viagra AGV.

Speaker 2: Did you have a question about it?

Speaker 1: I did, yeah.

Speaker 2: I'm hoping you can help me out.

Speaker 1: I received it, and the quantity is correct.

Speaker 2: It says 100 milligrams, but I don't see anywhere that the prescription identifies itself as—

Speaker 1: Viagra AGV.

Speaker 2: It's not written on the bottle anywhere.

Speaker 1: It's not written on the pills anywhere, and I know when I, you know, ordered it, the advertisement—

Speaker 2: that you see, you know, obviously it's a generic advertisement, but the bottle shows that it—

Speaker 1: identifies itself as AGV, and the pill does as well, but it's not.

Speaker 2: Yeah, so the AGV won't be on the pill, but what does the marking on your pill say?

Speaker 1: What should it say for it to be the AGV?

Speaker 2: Yeah, but what does yours say, so I can just validate here, because I need to see if it—

Speaker 1: matches to the script that they wrote for you.

Speaker 2: Hang on a second here.

Speaker 1: I need to get my glasses.

Speaker 2: Sure, no worries.

Speaker 1: It has the letters AC and the numbers 340.

Speaker 2: Got it.

Speaker 1: So, I thought I could confirm the pharmacy didn't make a mistake.

Speaker 2: The only thing you should have seen on yours is 100, and that's it.

Speaker 1: So, I'm going to notify them, and they're going to send you the correct order.

Speaker 2: You'll receive this in three to four business days.

Speaker 1: The one that you have, you're more than welcome to keep or dispose.

Speaker 2: We'll send you the correct one.

Speaker 1: So, what is the one that I currently have?

Speaker 2: It says it on the label right on the bottle, sir.

Speaker 1: It's a generic Viagra, standard.

Speaker 2: So, I do not have the AGV?

Speaker 1: Yeah, that's why I just said that we would send you the correct one, sir.

Speaker 2: Okay, okay.

Speaker 1: And what should the new pill say on them to identify them as AGV?

Speaker 2: 100.

Speaker 1: That's all it will say is 100?

Speaker 2: Yeah, exactly.

Speaker 1: Okay, okay.

Speaker 2: And so, do I send these—

Speaker 1: I think you answered that, but do I send these back to you or just wait for them?

Speaker 2: No, like I mentioned, you can just hold on to them, dispose of them.

Speaker 1: We'll send you the correct one.

Speaker 2: Okay, and how long will that take until they arrive?

Speaker 1: Three to four business days.

Speaker 2: Okay, wonderful.

Speaker 1: Anything else you need from me?

Speaker 2: No, you're all set.

Speaker 1: Hope you have a good day, sir.

Speaker 2: I appreciate your time.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: No problem.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
